BBEX3.M.SDD.EUR.CA.AB.A01: Exchange rates for the euro in Sudan / EUR 1 = SDD ... (selling)

General: The Sudanese pound (SDG) has been in circulation since 10 January 2007, when it was introduced at a rate of SDD 100 = SDG 1. Until 30 June 2007, exchange rates were listed in SDD (Sudanese dinar); for exchange rates from July 2007, see BBEX2:M:SDG:EUR:CA:AB:A01.
Comment on 2007-06: Listed in SDG from July 2007; see BBEX2:M:SDG:EUR:CA:AB:A01.
